<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Possible Duping Bug Causes Server Downage</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, July 31 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 8:02 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/965048557,15690,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> A critical, game threatening bug was discovered and verified.  The bug was fixed, I called people into work, and I had the servers shut down for an emergency update.  This doesn't happen often, but when it does, we must act quickly. <br><br>If something similar were to happen again in the future I'd bring them down again. <br><br>To those of you whose evenings were disrupted, I apologize. We will endeavour to minimize these occurrences.  To the Verant employees who had to direct this operation and/or come into work, I'm also sorry. <br><br>No one likes downtime, not us, not the players. <br><br>That said, to the complainers and flamers in this thread: think for a moment, and think about the game as a whole. Some of you act like kids who are mad at their parents for not letting them play in the street. My god, do you think we bring down servers like this for giggles? <br><br>To everyone else, again, sorry for the disruption. <br><br>Guys, we don't publicly document severe bugs like this -- you never know when something might not be all the way fixed, or perhaps when something related to it still is problematic. <br>That said, you don't really have to speculate much on what sort of bug we'd consider game threatening. <br><br>-Brad</font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem965048422,46133,"></a>
<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>End of boards at Everquest.com?</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, July 31 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 8:00 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
