<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Change to consent command</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Thursday, July 20 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 11:05 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/964109153,63713,.html">comment</a> on this article [1 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Verant announced today that due to increased corpse looting situations, as of the next patch it will be impossible to loot a players corpse after you have received a /consent. The /consent and /corpse commands will be left in game only to work as a tool to allow corpse dragging. <br></font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem964035228,90569,"></a>
