<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Ranger Fix</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Saturday, July 15 by <a href="mailto:vumil@brellserilis.net">Vumil</a> @ 2:01 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/963644503,14291,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Now correct me if I'm wrong, but wouldn't higher dmg output make it WORSE for us? <br><br><b>It depends on how we do it. In this case the plan is to enhance damage output from archery under certain conditions, giving rangers an incentive to back out of melee range for a few seconds. <br><br>If rangers can make a *big* hit from time to time at a greater delay rather than a *bunch* of smaller hits at a lesser delay, the desired affects might be obtainable. <br><br>- Gordon</b><br></font><br><br><br>
