<a name="newsitem963482448,59362,"></a>
<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Ranger Balance</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Thursday, July 13 by <a href="mailto:vumil@brellserilis.net">Vumil</a> @ 5:00 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/963482448,59362,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> A post made on the everquest gameplay forum:<br><br>Jolt is no real improvement for Rangers. <br><br>It's still a level 55 spell (Rangers see taunting problems earlier than this), it still costs just as much mana, it's still resistable, and the casting time was reduced from 3.5 secs to only 2.5 secs. Almost every other Ranger I know and have heard agrees that for this spell to be useful it needs to have about a 1.5 casting time and be unresistable or close to it. When a red con Sky mob is aggro on you hitting for 300 damage, trying to get a 2.5 sec spell off that might very well be resisted anyway is no help at all. <br><br>Verant, if you're going to make an honest change/improvement, please don't toss something out to humor players without thorough testing or feedback.<br><br><b>It was a 1 second improvement, or roughly a 30% improvement in casting time. I'd call that "real". Perhaps the misunderstanding is the typical one on this board, that an enhancement is "useless" unless it unbalances the class. Of course since we try not to make changes that do that, we're in a bit of a catch-22.<br><br>We are considering upping damage output for rangers though. <br><br>- Gordon</b><br><br>Up there damage so they taunt more, oh yah good idea!<br></font><br><br><br>
