<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Gordon Sheds Light on Future Changes</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Tuesday, June 20 by <a href="mailto:jester1176@home.com">Gunganus</a> @ 4:55 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/961494919,33211,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> From the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/053682.html">Everquest Gameplay Forum</a><br><br>Hello all, <br><br>                          I thought I'd bring a quick list of some things decided in today's tuning meeting. There's not much information here<br>                          besides what I'll list, but please feel free to comment:<br><br>                          * Concerning Nagafen and Vox: We're looking into a way to keep Nagafen and Vox as reasonable encounters for<br>                          the high-30s-50s characters without having the high 50s+ killing them constantly with little opposition. <br>                          * We'll be extending the "Rez-for-XP" window from 2 hours to 3 hours in light of size and difficulty of some of the<br>                          new zones.<br>                          * VZ/TZ move: See other thread.<br>                          * We're looking at a way to stop players from bypassing the need for a rogue by using an NPC to open pickable<br>                          doors. In other words, make friends with your local rogue  <br>                          * Poison update is expected on Test next week.<br>                          * "Jolt" will have its casting time lowered.<br>                          * The Hole is expected to go live this week.<br><br>                          -Gordon</font><br><br><br>
