<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Word on Trakanon</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, June 12 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 3:36 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/960842181,36356,.html">comment</a> on this article [1 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Found this excerpt on the EQnecro site. It is a question to Abashi about the toughness of Trakannon, the poison dragon who inhabits Sebilis. Interesting.<br><br><i>Well we were exploring in sebilis last night, and were a few hours in. We came to a big huge open room, then we see "Soando shivers and shakes" then right in front of me I see Trakanon! The lvl 60 with us conned him...red. Then he agroed. First aoe wave, 10dead...second aoe wave, 10more. Then his guardians came, hitting for 300+. He himself hit for dual 650's I heard from my groupmate. What I want to know, is do you think he is fair and "doable" in his current state? Yeah I agree he should be very hard, but an AoE dot that had to be at least 300dmg a tick and an AoE DD that was 800 or more damage...along with his guards bashing for 300...clerics arent gonna keep up with that.<br>Anyway abashi, would you tell me if that sounds right to you? It doesnt seem so...and if it is...I fear veeshan =)</i><br><br><b>Players have always surprised us with their ability to easily overcome situations that we first thought were undoable, so I don't think it will be too long before some, somewhere, show's Trakanon whats what. It just takes a little while to refine the strategy.<br><br>-Gordon</b><br><br><br></font><br><br><br>
