<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Additional Patch changes</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Wednesday, June 7 by <a href="mailto:vumil@brellserilis.net">Vumil</a> @ 3:53 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/960367999,66983,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> This morning I was handed a list of spell changes that didn't make it into the patch message. I'll put up an addendum later today, but here's the list for review:<br><br>- Banshee Aura has had its duration increased.<br>- Scale of Wolf and Spirit of Scale will no longer be canceled by being the target of a melee attack. Ranged attacks and spells will still cancel the spell.<br>- Shaman can now cast Charm Animal<br>- Some enchanter and shaman spells have had their casting times/mana costs altered.<br>- Augment, Glamour of Kintaz, Rapture, and Clarity II have had their mana cost lowered.<br>- Root spells that cause damage (Druid roots, Hungry Earth) now work properly.<br><br>-Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
