<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>To the Good Guilds of Brell</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Sunday, May 28 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 3:13 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/959544835,26777,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Lerdar sends this:<br><br>To the Good Guilds of Brell Serelis<br><br>Hail and well met, leaders and members of the fine guilds that defend<br>justice, kindness, and truth on Brell Serelis!  We have many, many such guilds on our server.   Each are great in their own way.   A thought has crossed my mind to make us greater still.<br><br>Brell has always been a relatively peaceful and quiet server.  There aren't a whole lot of non-guild raids, wars, or events.  Because of this, our guilds have generally found it easiest to go through life on their own, with little need for active alliances and the like.   This is not a bad system. However, there are times when we need to be stronger, times when we need to band together and strike down evil, times where we just need support, times when one guild, no matter how great, can accomplish something.   No one guild can continuously fight to retake the lands that evil has taken from us.  No one guild can be there across the world to help that person getting killed feet from safety, or to respond to evil uprisings and attacks. Overall, no one guild can accomplish all the goals of good.<br><br>That is why no one guild must stand alone to do so any longer.  I am issuing an invitation to all the good guilds of Brell to come to a conference.  At this conference, we will lay the groundwork for a world-wide alliance of all the guilds that are interested.  The exact functions that this alliance would perform , and how it would carry these out ,will be up to us as we carry this on in further meetings, until things are finalized and implemented.  It is my goal to have all the good guilds of Brell united through a council of representatives to keep communications open, organize ongoing operations in the name and intent of good, and make Norrath better for the good people that inhabit it.<br><br>We would like to see 2-5  representatives from all the good guilds here. The number of people from each guild in no way affects the decision making process at this stage. We will set a more formal and concrete representative system once we have the basic workings of the alliance laid out.  We will, within the council, eventually elect people to key positions such as military operations, economics, public relations, and more as we determine needs.  With cooperation from all ,we will make this a grand alliance that is never resting in it's battle against evil.  Come, help achieve that dream.<br><br>Lerdar</font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem959348942,96682,"></a>
