<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> There has been an update to the story of Dosoloth, originally posted by Humwawa D'Estain. Check it out by going <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/roleplay/dosoloth1.htm">here</a> or visiting our <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/roleplay/index.htm">Roleplaying</a> section. Here is a excerpt:<br><br><i>I could feel my heart's decay there in the blackness. I could feel it dying, what little part of it which had been revived from its umbral repose flaring as a shooting star and failing, failing into the ether, rotten and cold. <br><br>My fist tightened over the hilt of my blood red blade. My teeth ground together, my jaw tightened. My muscles tensed under the iron shell of my armour, prepared to strike the false creature down there in the solace of her secret lair. <br><br>Yet I could not bring my spirit to comply to my body's will. <br></i><br></font><br><br><br>
