<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Thalanar wrote<br><br>I would just like to thank all those who attended the bakers brownie raid tonight. Overall, it was a complete success. In three hours we managed to get 17 brownie parts, which worked out to approx 2 per baker, and no deaths (that I'm aware of)! There were far too many people there to list here, but you know who you are, and I thank you.<br><br>This was a great success for the baking community for bringing us closer together and getting us those coveted brownie parts, a success for the Brell community because it involved a very wide range of people (I think 17 to 54) to work together towards a common goal at one event, and a success for me because I have never tried organizing something of this scale. While things didn't go perfect, they never do, it went quite well and I have everyone who participated to thank.<br><br></font><br><br><br>
