<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>A gnomes Tale: Travel Across Kunark (pt3)</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Thursday, May 11 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 11:23 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/958105404,43452,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> The Yard trash of the Gods. That is what they claim wanders around the gates of Karnor's castle. Well, this gnome could use some trash! (cackle) Through the mountain hills I found a curious cave with others resting. They pointed within and told me that this cavern led to the Dreadlands. I had heard of these new lands, it is where many of the first landed as they teleported by way of druidic or wizardly magic. <br><br>As the cavern emptied out into a great expanse of desolate rock and scattered patches of grass, I saw some ruins in the distance. I could hear the shouts of adventurers and the roar of spellfire coming from them so I headed in under the shadows of darkness to investigate.<br><br>It was here I was met by a most curious sight. A lizard man in armor of pure blue, with strange sounds eminating from his person. I didn't recognize this figure at first but as he hailed me i knew it was my friend Quemn Wyndrunner. He removed his mask and then replaced it, his image shifting and bending before my very eyes. <br><br>It was here I met with my hunting companion from the other night, the shaman Ancere and many other new faces. I was invited to join a party of very seasoned adventurers and was reuinted with some old friends. The Champion of the Scale was among them, Sindarre. We had many good laughs and conversation until a large animal came bearing down on us. It resembled a chicken, but was much more fierce (and large!). <br><br>A curious place indeed. I picked up a nice weapon from one of the spider persons when I reached for it and its leg broke off in my hand. Perhaps i can use this as a weapon, it seemed to be embrued with magical properties. I think i will visit this place again, when i am more prepared in mind and body.<br><br>/ooc  The weapon I got was neat, although not very powerful. A Drachnid's Hind Leg, Dam 6, Del 27 Magic Weight 0. Looks like a minotaur horn. Dropped by a Drachnid. Also got a few pieces of ruined scale, which looks like green chainmail armor when worn.<br><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/dread-bard.gif">An Iksar Bard</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/dread-sindarre.gif">Sindarre the Scaled Claw</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/dread-drov.gif">A Menancing Drolvarg</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/dread-chicken.gif">Scary chickens</a><br></font><br><br><br>
