<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>New Message Board Features</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, May 8 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 9:16 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/957795370,92275,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> EZBoard, the greatest message board on the planet, has released a long set of new features and fixes. You will be able to see total views and hits to each of your posted message topics, as well as be able to rate topics. The complete list of changes was:<br><br>SPELL CHECK<br>You will now be able to Spell Check your New Posts, Replies and Edits.<br><br>(I'm really glad to see this feature!)<br><br>TOPIC VIEWS COUNTER (admin layout option)<br>Each time a user views a topic, this counter will be increased by 1. This will allow others to see how many times a particular topic has been read.<br><br>NOTE it only works for some forum styles.<br><br>TOPIC RATING (admin layout option)<br>Each registered user will now be able to cast their own vote (from 1 to 5)on the quality of the topic. The topic will have a graphical icon (1 to 5 of them) to represent its value.<br><br>AUTOMATIC SUBMISSION TO SEARCH ENGINES<br>Admins can submit their ezboard to search engines (PROMOTE link) just by clicking on a couple of buttons. It is important to make sure your search keys are as accurate as possible (GENERAL link).<br><br>USER'S CAN CHOOSE THEIR OWN PASSWORD<br>Registration will become a little easier. Users will be able to choose their own password when they register. They'll still need to validate their account by clicking on a link that will be sent to them via email.<br><br>ADMIN EMAIL TO USERS<br>ezboard admins will be able to send a private message via email to all of their users. This is a great way to let the community members know of new features and improvements.<br><br>BORDER OPTION (admin layout option)<br>There will be an option to turn off and on borders in your ezboard. The border color will also be configurable in your COLORS CUSTOMIZATION area. The Border option will give ezboads a "cleaner look and feel". <br><br>FORUM LISTING<br>You'll now also be able to alternate the background color/image in your forum listings area.<br><br>IMPROVED NAVIGATION <br>No need to use the Back button on your browser!<br>For example: ---- yourezboard > yourforum<br><br>COLOR CUSTOMIZATION SCREEN SHOTS<br>Screen Shots of the color customization options<br>in the control center.<br><br>AUTOMATED SEARCH ENGINE SUBMISSION<br>ezboard provides an automated submission of your ezboard to most of the major search engines. Click on the Promote Link in your control center under the ezboard tab.<br><br>BUG FIXES<br><br>- Fixed New Forums that have a web ID of a banned user<br>- Fixed duplicate page number in the topic view<br></font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem957785409,11476,"></a>
<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>A Gnomes Tale: Travel across Kunark (pt2)</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, May 8 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 6:30 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/957785409,11476,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> It was morning when I first heard the shouts echoing through the valley. Brave adventurers were assembling boldly outside the entrance to an enourmous fort constructed of wood and stone. It was there I met my new friends, the wise shaman Ancere and the veteran monk, Senn. There was to be a giant hunt, and with my recent run-in with the mountain people the day before still fresh in my mind, I was all too happy to join them. Grabbing some chips of bone from my spell components, I recited the ancient words and brought forth a servant of the dead. And quickly we entered into battle.<br><br>One of the tump folk dropped a mysterious golden earring. I had heard of the Forest Loop but had never seen it. It was decided it would go to someone wiser than I, but I do remember a little about it.<br><br>Tomorrow I think i will head into the mines of Nurga. A cleansing of some of the vile goblins found there is in order. Perhaps I will even find some interesting treasure to report.<br><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/day2giants.gif">Battling giants outside their home</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/forestloop.gif">The Forest Loop</a><br><br></font><br><br><br>
