<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>A Gnomes Tale: Travel across Kunark (pt1)</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Friday, May 5 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 2:27 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/957554867,5905,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> There's been a lot of hubbub about the giants inhabiting the frontier mountain range on Kunark. Tales of gigantic weapons, magical earrings and all sorts of other nonsense which would be temptation for treasure hunters to head there and risk losing their heads. I decided to put on my best walking slippers and summon me a skeletal companion (to hold my wardrobe and bags of course) and head on out. I had been previously holding camp at the beautiful (but slightly eerie) Lake of Ill Omen, and was just a hop skip and a lob to these new lands.<br><br>After passing some goblin infested holes and a beautifully constructed Sarnack fort (they didnt seem to like gnomes hrmph!) I entered the majestic mountain range. Oh my, were the rocks big! In fact, i was a mere spec while i sat on one of the stones. <br><br>Shortly after getting my bearings I saw one of the mountain natives tredging along in the valley below. I decided to introduce myself when suddenly, i was attacked! The giant's strength was enormous, but in the end I prevailed. He had a mysetious LARGE sword which was on his person. Since he was no longer living, i decided to try to stuff it in my pack, unfortunately it was too large (about the size of 6 gnomes!). <br><br>Quite rattled, i decided to move on. To the south, a mytserious rock formation was carved into the side of the mountain. I dare not get closer, it was guarded by many angry looking goblins. Some with the names of Dirtcallers, Plaguebringers, Rockchanters and Bonecharmers. Ghastly as it was, they failed to notice me as I kept my distance and moved around them with the deft agility all gnomes possess. <br><br>I think i like this place. It has character, danger and excitement. I will share more with you as it is uncovered.<br><br>Be Well!<br>-- Delsonora Blackthorne<br><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/gnometale/bigrocks.gif">Big Rocks</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/gnometale/gianttump.gif">A Giant Tump!</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/gnometale/ironback.gif">Sword the size of 6 gnomes!</a><br>Image: <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/gnometale/gobcave.gif">Strange Caves</a></font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem957534464,87827,"></a>
