<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Necromancer Ressurection: Convergence Details</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Friday, May 5 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 12:14 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/957503661,77004,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> As posted from EQNecro:<br><br>I gathered Gordon's posts from the EverQuest Gameplay Forum for your viewing. As you will see, Convergence (the ressurection spell) has been confirmed by Gordon. Sounds like we won't be using it too much though...<br><br>In any case, it seems that someone has already used Convergence and is willing to talk about it. In Gordon's post about the spell (see below), someone says that in order to use the spell, you need an Essence Emerald. To get this component, you need to cast Sacrifice on someone. You cannot cast Sacrifice on yourself. The sacrificed person cannot ressurected and will lose XP. Also, this person has to be level 45+ and can't be level 50 or 60 to avoid maxed out level 50 non-Kunark players and level 60 Kunark players from willingly taking the XP loss.<br><br>So, after casting Sacrifice you get an Essence Emerald. These are supposedly unstackable, no drop, but not lore.<br><br>Thus, if this information is correct, you also need the Sacrifice spell. And unlike what we thought so far, all that Sacrifice does it kill someone so you can get the Essence Emerald required for Convergence. And the same component required to cast Convergence is used for both Infusion and Trucidation.<br><br>Well, that is it. To tell you the truth, I don't think this is too bad. I bet we will see some uses for Convergence.<br></font><br><br><br>
