<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Verant taking steps against twinking</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Wednesday, May 3 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 3:46 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/957386784,32960,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> >>I'd like to hear why I bothered to get to a level where my spells don't work on people below 39. I feel this strips the class of most of it's power after lvl 51. <br><br>One of the limiting factors on what spells could do before was based upon what it would do if used as a twinking mechanism. The level 49 spells put us right up against this ceiling. When we created the new buffs, we decided to put the cut-off. You can still use your level 49 series on people a ways below you in level.<br><br>- Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
