<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Veeshans Peaks</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Thursday, April 27 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 11:44 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956853842,12749,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Just for a bit of clarification, back when the planes were brought online, John Smedley commented that people just don't die in planes, they die hard. Veeshan's Peak makes the planes look easy. There exists a non-negligible chance that not only will you die there, but you might not be able to raise the necessary forces to allow recovery of your corpse. It is *very* dangerous. <br>In order to avoid any appearance of impropriety in the zone, as sometimes follows when we've assisted in corpse recoveries in other zones due to claimed bug-deaths, we're not going to risk that for Veeshan's Peak. Veeshan's Peak is incredibly dangerous, and in order to guarantee that everyone is operating under the same set of conditions, we've elected to make the zone "enter at your own risk". <br><br>That said, there are no known bugs in the zone that would cause the death of a character, and it was tested extensively in the Ruins of Kunark beta. We will certainly investigate and eliminate any bugs that are reported, but we won't be reimbursing items or experience, nor will we be moving corpses or people within the zone.<br><br>-Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
