<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Kunark patch - Contains Word Virus</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Tuesday, April 25 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 10:40 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956677200,60792,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> It appears that we did patch two MS-Word '97 format Doc files that were infected with a relatively benign macro virus. <br><br>These viruses can only infect other files (and then only other Doc files) if they are opened in your word processor, so people who didn't open them prior to right now need not be alarmed. We at Verant proactively work to eliminate the possibility that things such as this happen, however some safeguards were unintentionally bypassed as party of the Kunark opening. We've closed this minor loophole and customers should not have to worry about anything such as this happening in the future. <br><br>We would like to extend our apologies to everyone on this matter.<br><br><br>Gordon Wrinn<br>Internet Relations Manager<br>Verant Interactive, Inc.<br></font><br><br><br>
<a name="newsitem956676991,7619,"></a>
<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Info regarding Scale of Wolf spell</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Tuesday, April 25 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 10:36 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956676991,7619,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> A new expansion spell was discussed on the EQ boards and Abashi stopped by to answer. Our druids/shammie may find it interesting.<br><br>>>>First off, why does it drop when you are hit EVEN IF you don't hit back ? <br>It works just like invisibility. We wanted to give people the means to travel faster without that travel method turning into another offensive tactic. <br><br>>>>Secondly, why does it overwrite SoW ? Verant doesn't need to stack actual spell effects to make them stack as being 'on' or 'off' - surely one spell can supercede in effect without overwriting<br><br>It overwrites SoW because it has the same effect and it does more to that effect. It's the way the spell hierarchy works. This really can't be changed.<br><br>>>>Um, this has exploit written all over it. <br><br>We'll probably have to make the spell group-only in the near future. I'll send a note to GZ.<br><br>-Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
