<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Kunark first impressions and shots</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Monday, April 24 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 4:03 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956610218,19339,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Well, i got Kunark cd today finally and installed it. The first thing you will notice is you will need to repatch. You also should do K Patch, which will download a zone or two for you. <br><br>I created an Iksay shammie. Well, unless you have a lot of patience i do not recommend the Iksar right now. First, the city is immense. There are not surprinsgly tons of iksar. There was actually waiting lists for groups in the main city, killing some of the yellow spawns (froglok slaves).<br><br>The newbie zone out of East Cabilis is horrid. It is called the Field of Bone. I cant tell you how many red cons i saw here, trains of 20-30 emerrald spiders killing everything in sight. The lag, was completely unreal. Be prepared to walk around blind also, Iksar have terrible night vision (see: paineel on launch)<br><br>Then, i deleted my iksar. I logged in my 22 druid, and went the traditional way to Kunark, on the boat. Boats depart from Butcherblock and Oasis. If you leave from BB you land in a somewhat friendly high elven outpost. From oasis, you land in the evil lands, i dont know which zone actually didnt go that way.<br><br>You board shuttles, and join up with an unbelievably immense ship, <br>The Maiden Voyage. After about a 5 min boat ride, you are in Fironia Vie, a high elf outpost. Here, i lasted about 15 mins before i was slain. But, i brought back some shots of what to expect.<br><br>Enjoy.<br><br><a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark1.gif">http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark1.gif</a><br><a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark2.gif">http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark2.gif</a><br><a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark4.gif">http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark4.gif</a><br><a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark5.gif">http://www.brellserilis.net/images/kunark/kunark5.gif</a><br><br><br></font><br><br><br>
