<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Interesting Conspiracy Theory</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Friday, April 21 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 6:36 PM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956360176,35761,.html">comment</a> on this article [1 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Found this on EQ Official board. It contains an interesting theory about all of these unbelievable RoK delays, and Abashi's rebuttal.<br><br>>>>"The GM informed him that Verant would be staggering shipments of Kunark. He told him that they were worried about the initial burst of players to Kunark and that as a result they would be limiting the amount of copies of the game initially."<br><br>This is completely false and I'll go so far as to say that this didn't happen. It is so far removed from the truth that I'm not willing to accept that anyone employed by Verant could have made a statement to this effect. I would caution everyone reading this to take note when someone speaks of information obtained by "a friend" and provided by an unnamed GM. Let's face it, nearly everyone logs anything told to them by a GM in game, and has no problem naming names in public when they feel that a real injustice has been committed. <br><br>The articles assertion that we somehow purposely engineered the admittedly unacceptable problems with shipping is unfathomable. We have measures in place on our side (including some impressive new code that has been in for over a month now) that should reduce or eliminate any concerns over zone-crashes due to over-population.<br><br>Now that that is out of the way, there are several posts here on the board by John Smedley that give the most up-to-date information that we have in regards to the shipping issues. We are committed to doing right by our cusotmers in this matter, and hope that you'll hang in there while we get everything sorted out. Running EverQuest has been an unending stream of "firsts" in the gaming world, and we'll learn from these issues as well.<br><br>Thanks,<br><br>-Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
