<font face="Verdana" color="#D0B078" size="3"><b>Plane of Sky Items</b></font> 
<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">Posted: Tuesday, April 18 by <a href="mailto:delsonora@brellserilis.net">Delsonora</a> @ 8:34 AM EDT<br>
<font face="Verdana" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
Add a <a href="http://www.brellserilis.net/news/talkback/956064843,9325,.html">comment</a> on this article [0 Comments]</font><br>

<br><br><font face="Verdana" size="2"> Hello all,<br>I've noticed that quite a few people are upset about the quality of some of the Plane of Sky items that have been found so far. <br><br>Part of the problem is due to the fact that the most powerful items still have yet to be acquired. Once you start seeing these items come out of the plane, you will understand what I meant when I said "There are items in the Plane of Sky that make other planar items look like rusty weapons". <br><br>The other part of the problem is that some of the items that have been found so far are indeed underpowered. Since we were entering uncharted territory with many of our ideas for these items, we erred on the side of making them underpowered, thus avoiding the problems that occur should we have to downgrade them later. That said, while some of the items that have been found so far are appropriately powered, many are not. <br><br>Though I will not comment on any particular item at this time, we will be reevaluating the Plane of Sky items in the near future, probably after the initial excitement from the Kunark release. <br><br>-Gordon<br></font><br><br><br>
